Supervision of Administrative Regulations Governing Intake and Social Services.
The purpose of the proposed action is to repeal this regulation.
With reductions in state funding and personnel the department no longer has welfare services staff to carry out the supervision of local administration or the associated functions.
Under this authority the department certifies legal blindness for local social services departments when individuals apply for blindness-related social services or benefits.
The department will continue to provide such certification of legal blindness upon request; however, this is a procedural matter only and does not need a regulation.
The agency does not intend to hold a public hearing on the proposed repeal of this regulation after publication.
